From 76b79fce4e0f002339c82a94b7b2ae6bcb04a334 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 01:25:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(claude_cli): auto-retry on transient network errors
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When a claude -p invocation fails with a known-transient pattern
(Stream idle timeout, Unable to connect to API, ConnectionRefused,
FailedToOpenSocket, 5xx, etc.), `invoke_claude` now retries up to 3
times with exponential backoff (30s → 60s → 120s). This absorbs the
common "laptop resumed from sleep, network not yet up" scenario
without forcing a full Stage 01-04 rerun.

Non-transient failures (subprocess timeout, bad JSON, auth errors)
bypass the retry loop and propagate immediately.

ClaudeCliError now carries a `transient: bool` flag for callers that
want to distinguish. Defaults: max_retries=3, retry_base_delay=30s.
Set max_retries=0 to disable.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01RxnSjdy7R88RZt5uMdjbBH
